article.headline: New Orleans 74, Denver 73 (2 OT)
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- The last of Kyle Buggs' five 3-pointers came with 26 seconds left in double overtime and lifted New Orleans to a 74-73 victory over Denver on Saturday night. Buggs had left the game late in regulation after diving for a loose ball and emerging with a gash on his head. He was stitched up and returned for the second overtime to finish with a team-high 17 points for the Privateers (15-13, 9-6 Sun Belt). Denver (14-13, 6-9) had a chance to regain the lead with 15 seconds left in the second overtime when Rodney Billups went to the foul line. After missing both free throws, Billups grabbed a rebound and went back up with another shot, which he also missed. New Orleans grabbed that rebound and was able to run out the clock. Denver also had the ball with a chance to win in regulation after New Orleans' Victor Brown had tied the game at 62 with a tip-in. But trouble again befell Billups, who turned the ball over with 12 seconds left. New Orleans could not take advantage and the game went to the first overtime, which ended tied at 69 after the Privateers' Billy McDade hit a 3-pointer in the final minute. Yemi Nicholson scored 21 points for Denver, which led 33-25 at halftime. Erik Benzel added 18, including four 3-pointers, while Carvell McAlister scored 11. Bo McCalebb scored 16 points for New Orleans, while Nathaniel Parker scored 14 points on 5-of-7 shooting.
